                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Mass spectrometry",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Mass spectrometry",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Following extraction, the samples were filtered and subjected to chip-based nanoelectrospray DI-MS analysis in positive and negative mode using an Advion TriVersa Nanomate combined with a Thermo Scientific Q-Exactive HF high resolution mass spectrometer. In positive and negative ion modes, the signal was collected for 3 min and 1.5 min, respectively, between 70-600 m/z, using a Thermo Scientific Q Exactive high resolution mass spectrometer. A total of 3 technical replicates were measured per blood spot and the resultant signal was saved as a .raw Thermo file for each replicate. Run order was randomised based on farm and, if multiple countries were measured simultaneously, country.</p>",
